Istanbul Prices Rise 0.7 Percent in August, Chamber Says

-- B y   S e l c u k   G o k o l u k
-- 
2011-09-02T06:23:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-02/istanbul-prices-rise-0-7-percent-in-august-chamber-says.html
Prices in Istanbul,  Turkey ’s biggest
city, rose 0.72 percent in August, the city’s  chamber of
commerce  said.  Annual inflation in Istanbul slowed to 6.67 percent in the
month from 6.71 percent in July, the chamber said today.
Turkey’s state statistics agency will announce nationwide price
data for August on Sept. 5.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Selcuk Gokoluk in Istanbul at 
